	      <supportDesc>
		<support>
		  <p>A memorial stela: a prominent female figure over
		     a high mūḍa-type pedestal in ardhaparyaṅkāsana,
		    the dangling right foot on a footrest. Four female
		     attendants are seen on the left lower side somewhat
		     bent and holding a circular box (toilet). While
		     at the correspondign right, a female holds a mirror
		     (darpaṇa). The right side standing female holds
		     a cāmara, the left one a vessel on the shoulder.</p>
		  <dimension unit="cm">
		    <height>90</height>
		    <width>63</width>
		    <depth>11</depth>
		  </dimension>
		</support>
	      </supportDesc>
